                <note rend="inline" type="source">890E.01/101: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at Beirut</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Engert</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-11-19T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 19, 1941—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>210. Your No. 499 [<hi rend="italic">449</hi>], November 13, 10 p.m. The
                    Department does not understand the meaning or intent of the statement in
                    Catroux’ letter to Lyttelton that “the Franco-American Convention of April 4,
                    1924 extended to the Lebanon thus defined the guaranty of the United
                    States.”</p>
                <p>Please comment.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
